-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Almarai Co., Oman International Bank
-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 2012-05-29T13:25:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/persian-gulf-stocks-almarai-co-oman-international-bank.html
Oman’s  MSM30 Index (MSM30)  gained 1 percent
to 5,753.97, the highest level since May 8, at the 1 p.m. close
in Muscat. Saudi Arabia’s Tadawul All Share Index fell 0.3
percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Almarai Co. Ltd. (ALMARAI)   climbed as much as 2.2
percent to 69 riyals, before trimming gains to 68.25 riyals.
Saudi Arabia’s largest food producer said its board approved a
15.7 billion-riyal ($4.2 billion) five-year investment program
to boost output and develop products, according to a statement
to the Saudi bourse.  Oman International Bank SAOG (OIBB)   rose 1.7 percent to
0.238 rial, the highest level since April 30. The bank’s merger
with  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) ’s operations in the Persian Gulf country
is on schedule, Al Watan newspaper reported, without saying how
it obtained the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
